## Introduction
I’m a **Senior Lead Software Engineer at Chargebee** with 12+ years of experience spanning full-stack product development, distributed systems, and **GenAI-based platform architecture**. I build resilient infrastructure, intuitive developer tools, and intelligent systems that drive outcomes for global SaaS platforms.

My work blends **architectural depth with hands-on execution**—from frontend frameworks and backend orchestration to observability, multi-region scaling, and AI-first platforms. I’ve led major initiatives like **ERP integration frameworks, async job engines, and LLM-powered assistants**.

At Chargebee, I architected and own **Chargebee Copilot**, an AI-native assistant that automates billing and support workflows. It integrates **OpenAI, Anthropic, LangGraph, LangChain, Pinecone, and Langfuse** to deliver contextual, agent-driven RAG pipelines.  
**Impact**: *30% reduction in ticket inflow* and *50% faster first-response times*.

I also led the architecture for our **ERP & CRM Integration Platform**, reducing development effort by **80%** and enabling 10+ connector rollouts (including **NetSuite, QuickBooks, ZohoCRM, and HubSpot**). I bring deep domain expertise in **Accounts Receivables and billing automation**, especially within NetSuite ecosystems.

I operate at the intersection of **platform engineering, AI product thinking, and developer experience**—taking **0→1 ownership of complex systems** with clarity, empathy, and execution rigor.

Outside of Chargebee, I co-founded **[Revmonk](https://revmonk.io)**—a real-time lead intelligence tool that enriched high-intent web traffic and triggered auto-personalized outreach for marketing teams. I owned the entire stack (tracking, enrichment, orchestration, campaigns). We onboarded 50+ trial users and 2 paying customers before sunsetting due to operational costs—**sharpening my product instincts and founder mindset**.

I also contribute as a **mentor within my company**, a **volunteer with the CEG alumni network**, and a **tech advisor to early-stage startups** in my network. I’m part of the **API Review Council** and **engineering hiring committee** at Chargebee.

## 1. Chargebee Copilot – AI-Native Assistant

**Problem**  
Support teams were overwhelmed with repetitive billing queries, leading to high ticket inflow and delayed response times.

**Solution & Architecture**  
- Designed and led development of a **GenAI-powered assistant**.  
- **RAG pipelines** with billing-domain context.  
- **Custom agents** aligned with billing primitives (subscriptions, invoices, dunning).  
- Tech stack: **LangChain, LangGraph, Pinecone, Langfuse, Splunk, AWS**.

**Scale & Impact**  
- **~5,000 queries/day**.  
- Latency: **10–30s per query**.  
- Reduced ticket inflow by **30%**; improved first-response time by **50%**.

**Role**  
- **Tech Lead**, 3-person team.  
- End-to-end ownership: infra, pipeline design, monitoring, rollout.  
- Collaborated with product/support teams to refine Copilot behavior.

## 2. Chargebee Jobs Framework – Distributed Job Processing

**Problem**  
Chargebee needed a **fault-tolerant async system** to run subscription renewals, invoicing, reporting, and integrations — at **tens of millions of jobs/day** scale.

**Solution & Architecture**  
- Built a **DB-driven distributed job framework** (no Kafka/SQS).  
- Components: **Job Picker**, **Executor**, **Throttler**, **Config Manager (Vinyas)**.  
- Job types: recurring, site-segmented, transactional, SLA-based, idempotent (WIP).  
- **Observability**: Splunk dashboards, CloudWatch metrics, SLA breach alerts.

**Scale & Impact**  
- **~39M jobs/day**.  
- **Avg exec < 1.5s**, 95% < 3s.  
- Multi-tenant isolation + fairness (throttling).

**Notable Incident**  
- **Duplicate execution SEV** due to race conditions.  
- Solved with a **two-step picking protocol**: atomic `scheduled→picked` in DB, then atomic `picked→started` before execution. Eliminated duplicates.

**Role**  
- **Tech Lead alongside Architect**.  
- Owned schema design, idempotency semantics, and contention resolution.  
- Partnered with SREs for scaling/sharding strategy and monitoring.

**Architecture Diagram**  
![Jobs Framework Architecture](data:image/png;base64,)

## 3. Catalyst Sync Framework – Unified Integration Platform

**Problem**  
Integrations (NetSuite, QuickBooks, HubSpot, Intercom, etc.) were fragmented, slow to build, and hard to maintain.

**Solution & Architecture**  
- Built **Catalyst**, a **config-driven sync framework**.  
- Pluggable pipeline engine (Apache Camel + Java).  
- Config-driven integrations via JSON + client → reduced duplication.  
- Isolated **integration servers + schema** for scalability.  
- Fault tolerance: checkpointing, retries, DLQ.  
- Monitoring: Splunk dashboards, starvation reports, SLA dashboards.

**Scale & Impact**  
- Unified **~10 integrations** onto Catalyst.  
- **90k records/min throughput** (well above API limits).  
- Reduced new integration dev effort by **80%**.

**Notable Challenge**  
- **SuiteTax issue in NetSuite**: Tax sync failures due to tenant-specific config.  
- Fixed by moving **tax provider config from integration-level → tenant-level**.

**Role**  
- **Core Contributor & Tech Lead**.  
- Architected pipeline, config-driven model, monitoring.  
- Owned accounting integrations (NetSuite, Xero, QuickBooks).  
- Collaborated with SREs on sharding + operational SLAs.

**Architecture Diagram**  
![Catalyst Sync Framework Architecture](data:image/png;base64,)

## 4. Revmonk – Startup (Lead Intelligence Platform)

**Problem**  
Sales teams lacked **real-time lead intelligence**. Existing tools required manual enrichment and lacked automated outreach.

**Solution & Architecture**  
- Co-founded and built **Revmonk from scratch**.  
- **Tracking Layer**: ~10k–50k events/tenant/day.  
- **Queueing**: Redis + SQS, retries with backoff, DLQ for failures.  
- **Enrichment**: Clearbit, LinkedIn APIs with caching in Postgres + Redis.  
- **Outreach Automation**: SendGrid workflows, >95% deliverability.  
- **Frontend**: React + Next.js dashboard for sales teams.

**Scale & Impact**  
- **50+ trial users**, **2 paying customers**.  
- Pipeline processed **hundreds of thousands of events/day**.  
- Event → Outreach trigger in **seconds**.

**Notable Challenges**  
- API cost → solved with caching + tiered enrichment.  
- Deliverability issues → fixed with DKIM/SPF, warmed IPs, personalization.

**Role & Ownership**  
- **Co-Founder & Sole Engineer (with 1 intern)**.  
- Owned end-to-end stack: backend, frontend, infra, outreach.  
- Took part in **customer calls, demos, onboarding**.  
- Partnered with co-founder (sales/marketing).  

**Key Learnings**  
- Built **production-grade async infra** with retries & DLQs.  
- Gained **customer-first mindset** and balancing of tech vs. business.  
- First-hand experience in **0 → 1 product development**.
